                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14052874" author="hwellmann" created="Sat, 5 Jul 2014 14:21:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Regarding the underlying usecase and the discussion in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2645&quot; title=&quot;Add a (hidden) way to retrieve a local URL for a given bundle URL&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-2645&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-2645&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it would be nice to have an official OSGi API to do this kind of URL conversion - does anybody know why the proposed property never made it into a spec release? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d be happy with any alternative solution that does not force me to use reflection hacks (which is what I&apos;m doing now). If OSGi Alliance can&apos;t agree on an API, a container-specific API is still better than no API at all. Equinox has an &lt;tt&gt;org.eclipse.osgi.service.urlconversion.URLConverter&lt;/tt&gt; service for this purpose.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
